name: Two Six Code
title: TSC
definition: Identifies a code assigned to a trunk group or a CCS Link Set.
usageNotes: Required when the LA field is “Y” for established   trunk side service or CCS Link Set.
Optional when the LA field is not populated for   established trunk side service or CCS Link Set.
fieldNotes: The code set is unique to each established trunk   group or CCS Link Set and is provided to the   customer on the Firm Order Confirmation. The   TSC entry may then be populated by the customer   when ordering changes additions or deletions to an   existing trunk group or CCS Link Set.
